headline: FedEx Freight Taps New CEO, Chairman Ahead of 2026 Spinoff
summary: U.S.-Canada chief operating officer John Smith will be appointed CEO of the independent LTL, while vice chair Brad Martin will serve as chairman.

headline: FedEx buys SAF from Neste for express cargo delivery at LAX
summary: The 3 million gallons of fuel will be used for delivery at Los Angeles International Airport, and will account for roughly one-fifth of FedEx’s fuel consumption at the airport.
